<br>
With a sigh of relief her mind makes a quick decision and she turns along the path and heads for the note, knowing whatever the future holds for her that now is the time to relax and give her wounds time to heal.  Her body ached and her soul was crying silently within for rest and the trail wound leisurely up the side of a stream.  Not far from the main path she left she looks up and there stands the inn with inviting signs of life.<br>
<br>
As she neared a large troll opens the larger of the two doors and strolls out and she nods a greeting to him as she slips in the open door.  Scanning the room it is much as she left it and a sense of coming home flows through her very essense, as her eyes come to rest on a familiar figure sitting quietly in a corner, a corner she herself would chose at this juncture in her life.<br>
<br>
Keeping her cloak wrapped around her and her hood up around her face with only the emblem of a High Priestess of Rodcet Nife visiable to those around her she makes her way to the back table.<br>
<br>
"Hello Ranger, mind if a tired healer shares your table and perhaps a drink?", her eyes flash wearily towards Radgen but with a sign of mirth in them.<br>
<br>
 <p>Lodach Trueheart, High Priestess Of Rodcet Nife<BR>
The Tribunal Server<br>Elitist & Vagrants<br>
